An intranet is an internal company network. Its primary uses are  bring to people together, share key information, and foster a collaborative culture.
Intranets are repositories of company content, where employees and departments can access collateral they need to project management, training, to inform tasks, or to share with customers. Security is controlled at the admin level, ensuring only authorized employees can access, view, edit, or download information. 
Modern intranets use automation to simplify and streamline repetitive workflows, create reports, and keep employees connected through social media-like features such as chats and news feeds. 
